07/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov wrapped up a two-day visit to Russia on Saturday (6 September).
Talks between Parvanov and his Russian counterpart, Vladimir Putin, focused on economic co-operation, specifically the possibilities for intensifying contacts in the energy sector.
They discussed projects for increasing gas deliveries to the region from Russia via Bulgaria.
Putin also expressed the willingness of Russian firms to upgrade the third and fourth units of Bulgaria's Kozloduy nuclear power plant.
(AFP, BTA , Mediapool, News.bg - 06/09/03)
